                  <persName id="t18230409-118-victim1061" type="victimName">
                     JACOB 
                     HEWLINGS
                  <interp inst="t18230409-118-victim1061" type="surname" value="HEWLINGS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230409-118-victim1061" type="given" value="JACOB"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230409-118-victim1061" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230409-118-off630 t18230409-118-victim1061"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            . I am a <rs id="t18230409-118-viclabel631" type="occupation">straw-hat manufacturer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230409-118-victim1061 t18230409-118-viclabel631"></join>, and live in Hanway-street. The prisoner was nearly seven years in my service, and was entrusted to receive money for me; Miss Cummings owed me 1 l. 1 s. 6 d. The prisoner should account to me as soon as he received money; he never gave me the money, I asked him about it. It was not his duty to enter it in the books. I enquired of him about this account among others; he acknowledged that he had received it, and I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230409-118-person1062">
                  HARRIOT 
                  HAMPSHIRE
